4 STATE OF MAINE
5 SENATE
6 132ND LEGISLATURE
7 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
8 SENATE AMENDMENT “ ” to COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “A” to H.P. 381,
9 L.D. 613, “An Act to Amend the Maine Death with Dignity Act to Ensure Access by
10 Qualified Patients”
11 Amend the amendment in section 1 in subsection 11 by striking out all of the first
12 blocked paragraph (page 1, lines 23 to 25 in amendment) and inserting the following:
13 'The attending physician may waive a portion of the waiting periods required in this
14 subsection if, in the attending physician's medical opinion, it is in the best interests of the
15 qualified patient, given the qualified patient's condition, as long as the waiting period in
16 total is no less than 7 days.'
17 Amend the amendment by striking out all of section 4 and inserting the following:
18 'Sec. 4. 22 MRSA §2140, sub-§14, ¶H is enacted to read:
19 H. When a portion of the waiting periods under this section has been waived pursuant
20 to subsection 11, a note by the attending physician that, in the attending physician's
21 medical opinion, it is in the best interests of the qualified patient to waive a portion of
22 the waiting periods, given the qualified patient's condition, and what portion of the
23 waiting periods has been waived. The waiting period in total may not be less than 7
24 days.'
25 Amend the amendment by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
26 section number to read consecutively.
27 SUMMARY
2288 This amendment provides a waiting period in total of no less than 7 days.
